<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Assam</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #006400;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .state-details {
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: white;
            margin: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .state-details img {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        footer {
            background-color: #006400;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
            position: fixed;
            width: 100%;
            bottom: 0;
        }

        h2 {
            color: #333;
        }

        p {
            color: #555;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        h3 {
            color: #333;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul {
            color: #555;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Assam</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="state-details">
        <h2>Welcome to Assam</h2>
        <p>Assam, a beautiful state in northeastern India, is known for its tea gardens, rich biodiversity, and vibrant culture. The Brahmaputra River flows through this state, adding to its scenic beauty.</p>

        <h3>Key Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Capital:</strong> Dispur</li>
            <li><strong>Official Language:</strong> Assamese</li>
            <li><strong>Major Festivals:</strong> Bihu, Durga Puja</li>
            <li><strong>Specialty:</strong> Assam Tea, Silk</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Popular Tourist Attractions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Kaziranga National Park:</strong> A UNESCO World Heritage site known for one-horned rhinoceroses.</li>
            <li><strong>Kamakhya Temple:</strong> A sacred Hindu pilgrimage site.</li>
            <li><strong>Majuli:</strong> The largest river island in the world.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
